title: For Sale:  Pre-2006 Bushmaster AR-15 AR15 XM15-E2s 223 556 NR MADE in Windham
postcontent:
This is a very nice Bushmaster AR-15! When they were the best damn AR-15 platform on the market, prior to selling out. Many prefer this over Colt or other higher priced AR's. This was prior to moving operations to New York - and prior to Walmart beating the quality down.

This is not the newer, cheaper $750 Walmart Bushmaster or the carbon/carbine version that others are trying to sell you for $1500. This is the sought after and more desirable weapon back when they built them tight and heavier in Windham, ME. If you are not familiar, do some research and you will quickly gain an appreciation for this weapon and why they are desirable! (Read "HISTORY" below).

It also reads 5.56mm-.223 on the lower, indicating you can shoot 5.56mm rounds out of this gun, unlike some of the newer uppers.
Other notable details:
- 16" barrel.
- Flat top, optics ready.
- Larger charging handle.
- Full float aluminum forearm Tri-rail system.
- Aluminum tube with 6 position stock.
- Conformed Grip.
- CMI recoil pad.
- 30 round C- Products USGI hi-cap High capacity magazine.
- Dust Cover.
- Forward Assist.
- GG&G aluminum Sling mount.

BUSHMASTER HISTORY: In the beginning, Bushmaster Firearms International made their name as a well known maker of quality AR-15 type rifles owned by Richard Dyke. In 2006 he sold the company to Cerberus Capital Management, which in turn owned Freedom Group, which became Bushmaster's parent company that also owned other firearms manufacturer's including Remington and Marlin. Bushmaster production continued in Windham, Maine until March of 2011 when it was moved to Ilion, New York, to consolidate operations with other Freedom Group manufacturing. The facility in Windham was closed and the employees were laid off. (Source: http://www.grampasgunreviews.com/WindhamWeaponryMPC)

MARKINGS: "B.F.I. - Windham, ME, - U.S.A." = Bushmaster Firearms International.

SERIAL AND DATING: After contracting Bushmaster, it was determined this serial number (L223620) indicates it was made in 2001. Right in the heart of when these weapons were sought after and desired.

BARREL: 16 inch barrel with good bore and rifling. I *think* it is a 1/7 twist by other models I have viewed, but I could not find the stamp to tell you with certainty.

ACTION: Very smooth and crisp action. This was not test fired, however we did fire it with a snap cap and the trigger feels good and sounds like the hammer hit the snap cap appropriately.

This is the best information I have on this unique piece. I encourage you to do your own research or ask any questions you have. I will do our best to answer with the information we were given. Please view all pics carefully to appreciate it's condition.

title: For Sale:  Kimber 82 Government Target Rifle
postcontent:
This is a new CMP Kimber 82 Government that has had the stock refinished. The stock had decent grain, but of course had the nasty slash on the butt and a little on the forearm. Kimber apparently finished the rifles with some type of finish that had an orangish coloring mixed in. Not bad, but it certainly didn't let the grain come through. The pic showing the rifle and all parts is before the stock refinish. 

I stripped the factory finish, raised the grain, and sanded the stock to remove the cut mark. I then stained it dark walnut, and put on about 10-15 coats of tung oil. I finished it off with a steel wool buff followed by a coat of Minwax. It has a nice, satin finish. It is not perfectly smooth as you can see evidence of the grain in the finish. Unfortunately, there are a couple of minor handling marks already. 

The rifle was completely disassembled and the rust inhibitor removed from all parts. The barrel, bolt and trigger group are all rust-free and look just like they did when shipped from Kimber. The barrel has been cleaned and the trigger group disassembled, cleaned, and adjusted. There is very little creep or over travel now and the safety works perfectly. At the moment, I'd guess the trigger has an approx. 4-6 oz. pull and is set up for benchrest. For anything else, I'd suggest increasing the pull weight to 1 pound or greater. It is very easy to adjust the trigger on this rifle and factory instructions are included.

All of the documentation, tools, sights, packaging, etc. that came with the rifle will be included. I am not an FFL, so you'll have to make certain the FFL on your end will accept the shipment from me. I will need a copy of their FFL to present to UPS. Payment has to be made by USPS money order before the rifle will ship. I typically get it out via UPS ground the next day. My Ebay user is ferrarif1racefan and I have 100% feedback. I've sold a number of firearms online and have never had a single problem. 

If you have specific questions, please feel free to email me at: ferrarif1fan at hesenergy dot net. I also have plenty of other pics I'd be happy to send to you.
